body:
I compiled [this code](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=48ce3156989e38df4703a852f5189e68) on the playground:

```rust
#![feature(const_trait_impl)]

use core::ops::Deref;

trait ByteSlice: Deref<Target=[u8]> {}

struct Wrapper<B>(B);

impl<B: ByteSlice> Wrapper<B> {
    const fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.0.len()
    }
}
```

I got this error:

```text
error[[E0277]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/error-index.html#E0277): the trait bound `B: ~const Deref` is not satisfied
  --> src/lib.rs:11:16
   |
11 |         self.0.len()
   |                ^^^ the trait `~const Deref` is not implemented for `B`
   |
note: the trait `Deref` is implemented for `B`, but that implementation is not `const`
  --> src/lib.rs:11:16
   |
11 |         self.0.len()
   |                ^^^
help: consider further restricting this bound
   |
9  | impl<B: ByteSlice + ~const std::ops::Deref> Wrapper<B> {
   |                   ++++++++++++++++++++++++

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0277`.
```

When I [took the suggestion](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=4d9dd99716669baeef9fc8d8181f89b4) and added a `~const Deref` bound, I got an error stemming from the location of that new bound:

```rust
#![feature(const_trait_impl)]

use core::ops::Deref;

trait ByteSlice: Deref<Target=[u8]> {}

struct Wrapper<B>(B);

impl<B: ByteSlice + ~const Deref> Wrapper<B> {
    const fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.0.len()
    }
}
```

```text
error: `~const` is not allowed here
 --> src/lib.rs:9:21
  |
9 | impl<B: ByteSlice + ~const Deref> Wrapper<B> {
  |                     ^^^^^^^^^^^^
  |
  = note: only allowed on bounds on functions, traits' associated types and functions, const impls and its associated functions
```

### Version

Rust nightly 2022-10-16 b8b5caee04116c7383eb
